From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0035/N] shenandoahPassiveHeuristics: MAX2 size_t cast under CHERI

Same template-deduction collision as patches 0016/0019/0033.

`shenandoahPassiveHeuristics.cpp:57`:
  MAX2(max_capacity / 100 * ShenandoahEvacReserve, actual_free)

`max_capacity` is `size_t`; `ShenandoahEvacReserve` is `uintx`
(unsigned `__intcap` on purecap). The product is `__intcap`. The
second argument `actual_free` is `size_t`. MAX2's `T` cannot
deduce a single type.

Cast the first arg to `size_t`. The arithmetic
`max_capacity / 100 * ShenandoahEvacReserve` is bounded by
`max_capacity` (since ShenandoahEvacReserve is a percentage, ≤100)
so cannot overflow size_t.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0035)

--- a/src/hotspot/share/gc/shenandoah/heuristics/shenandoahPassiveHeuristics.cpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/share/gc/shenandoah/heuristics/shenandoahPassiveHeuristics.cpp
@@ -54,7 +54,8 @@
   // Do not select too large CSet that would overflow the available free space.
   // Take at least the entire evacuation reserve, and be free to overflow to free space.
   size_t max_capacity = ShenandoahHeap::heap()->max_capacity();
-  size_t available = MAX2(max_capacity / 100 * ShenandoahEvacReserve, actual_free);
+  // CHERI: ShenandoahEvacReserve is uintx (__intcap); cast back to size_t for MAX2
+  size_t available = MAX2((size_t)(max_capacity / 100 * ShenandoahEvacReserve), actual_free);
   size_t max_cset  = (size_t)(available / ShenandoahEvacWaste);

   log_info(gc, ergo)("CSet Selection. Actual Free: " SIZE_FORMAT "%s, Max CSet: " SIZE_FORMAT "%s",
